WEBVTT

00:00:02.160 --> 00:00:06.330
That's how you die!
Over-dependent and abandoned!

00:00:06.330 --> 00:00:09.160
In four days, on August 15!

00:00:09.160 --> 00:00:14.410
The world has set your death
in stone! There's no escaping it!

00:00:14.410 --> 00:00:17.580
But I refuse to accept that!

00:00:18.450 --> 00:00:20.370
I'm going to fight the world!

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:25.200
I will save Mayuri!

00:00:39.580 --> 00:00:41.370
The coin locker...

00:00:44.620 --> 00:00:46.330
In front of the Dai Building...

00:00:47.910 --> 00:00:50.290
The IBN 5100...

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:09.410
suu juuoku mono kodou no kazu sae

00:01:09.410 --> 00:01:16.080
anata ni wa matataki teido no saji na toukyuu

00:01:16.080 --> 00:01:21.290
kako ni torawarete mirai o nageku mo

00:01:21.290 --> 00:01:27.200
chiri hitotsu gosan o yurusanu hitsuzen

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:33.330
mugen ni hirogaru yume mo egaku mirai mo

00:01:33.330 --> 00:01:39.160
bokutachi ni yurusareta kyoei no kenri

00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:45.410
yuugen sore wa futatsu no hari ga shimesu

00:01:45.410 --> 00:01:50.000
zankoku na yakujou to sentaku e

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:52.250
Hacking to the Gate

00:01:52.250 --> 00:01:59.160
da kara ima ichi byou
goto ni sekaisen o koete

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:04.080
kimi no sono egao mamoritai no sa

00:02:04.080 --> 00:02:11.080
soshite mata kanashimi
no nai jikan no ruupu e to

00:02:11.080 --> 00:02:17.750
nomi komarete yuku kodoku no kansokusha

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:42.580
Okabe! What's going on?!

00:02:45.330 --> 00:02:47.700
Okay! This should do it!

00:02:47.700 --> 00:02:49.870
Stop!

00:02:52.790 --> 00:02:55.870
The IBN 5100's in a coin locker?

00:02:55.870 --> 00:02:57.620
Moeka confessed!

00:02:57.620 --> 00:02:59.410
And it hasn't been picked up yet!

00:02:59.410 --> 00:03:00.250
So...?

00:03:00.250 --> 00:03:01.700
Isn't it obvious?!

00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:05.790
-I'm gonna bust into it and--
-Calm down and try to remember.

00:03:05.790 --> 00:03:07.500
Remember what?!

00:03:07.500 --> 00:03:09.620
Everything so far.

00:03:09.620 --> 00:03:11.830
Even after all the D-mails you've undone,

00:03:11.830 --> 00:03:15.540
the IBN 5100 has still eluded you.

00:03:15.540 --> 00:03:20.750
I think it might only be possible if
you return to the original world line.

00:03:20.750 --> 00:03:25.250
And the only way to do
that is to do things in order.

00:03:35.830 --> 00:03:38.370
Just when it's within arm's reach...

00:03:38.370 --> 00:03:41.080
At least we have a lead now.

00:03:42.410 --> 00:03:47.120
Kiryu Moeka will do
anything this FB person says,

00:03:47.120 --> 00:03:50.080
since FB's in charge of the Rounders, right?

00:03:50.080 --> 00:03:51.620
In which case...

00:03:56.410 --> 00:04:01.660
Maybe I'll find FB if
I stake out the IBN 5100...!

00:04:08.620 --> 00:04:10.620
What do you want?

00:04:13.580 --> 00:04:16.500
I... want to meet FB too...

00:04:16.500 --> 00:04:21.620
I thought you didn't want to?
That she'd hate you if she met you...

00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:25.410
I want to know the truth...

00:04:25.410 --> 00:04:28.040
Why?

00:04:29.410 --> 00:04:32.120
I don't know.

00:04:32.120 --> 00:04:36.040
Did you really think I'd cooperate with you?

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:46.120
Well, since there's no
talking sense into you anyway...

00:04:51.870 --> 00:04:53.200
Huh?!

00:04:53.200 --> 00:04:54.660
What's wrong?

00:04:54.660 --> 00:04:56.870
N-Nothing.

00:04:56.870 --> 00:05:00.200
Kiryu Moeka is with you?!
How did that happen?!

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:01.370
Seriously, she's--

00:05:01.370 --> 00:05:03.450
That's just how it turned out.

00:05:03.450 --> 00:05:06.000
I'll let you know if anything happens.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:09.080
Hey! Wait!

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:11.040
Urgh...

00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:12.080
Okarin?

00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:14.290
Huh? Yeah.

00:05:18.830 --> 00:05:21.200
What's the matter?

00:05:21.200 --> 00:05:23.290
It's just...

00:05:23.290 --> 00:05:28.250
It feels like Okarin and I haven't
talked at all in a long time.

00:05:34.330 --> 00:05:37.080
Oh, Big Sis Mayuri!

00:05:37.080 --> 00:05:39.950
Nae-chan!

00:05:39.950 --> 00:05:41.910
Too-too-roo!

00:05:41.910 --> 00:05:45.500
Too-too-roo to you too, assistant girl!

00:05:46.580 --> 00:05:48.410
Call me "Big Sis Kurisu."

00:05:48.410 --> 00:05:49.540
Hey, there.

00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:52.870
Hello. Sorry about yesterday...

00:05:52.870 --> 00:05:56.500
Tell Okabe I'm upping his rent 5,000 yen.

00:05:56.500 --> 00:05:57.910
O-Okay.

00:05:57.910 --> 00:06:00.500
Come to think of it,
I haven't seen that bum all day.

00:06:00.500 --> 00:06:02.540
He sick or something?

00:06:02.540 --> 00:06:05.290
They say idiots don't catch colds, though...

00:06:05.290 --> 00:06:09.250
Oh, I think he's out looking
for stuff for his experiments...

00:06:09.250 --> 00:06:10.700
Experiments, huh?

00:06:10.700 --> 00:06:13.290
Man, what a happy-go-lucky guy.

00:06:13.290 --> 00:06:14.200
Huh?

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:16.700
A student with a room all his own,

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:21.200
has friends like you guys,
and does whatever he wants...

00:06:21.700 --> 00:06:23.500
Doesn't get much better than that.

00:06:23.500 --> 00:06:25.200
But I'll tell you this...

00:06:25.200 --> 00:06:29.580
We hafta hurry, Dad!
The sale's about to end!

00:06:29.580 --> 00:06:31.450
Okay! Let's go, Nae!

00:06:31.450 --> 00:06:32.290
Yeah!

00:06:32.290 --> 00:06:34.000
Bye-bye, big sisters!

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:35.160
Bye-bye!

00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:37.500
What should we have for dinner?

00:06:37.500 --> 00:06:40.830
Hmm, lemme think...

00:06:51.160 --> 00:06:53.830
Old messages from FB?

00:06:56.620 --> 00:06:58.790
Can I see?

00:07:12.120 --> 00:07:16.750
"I think you made the right decision, M4.

00:07:16.750 --> 00:07:22.700
To be honest, no one has worked
as hard and intently as you, M4."

00:07:22.700 --> 00:07:24.290
"M4"...?

00:07:24.290 --> 00:07:27.750
The code name FB gave me.

00:07:27.750 --> 00:07:31.330
Only FB and I know it.

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:34.500
It's a secret.

00:07:34.500 --> 00:07:41.040
"Maybe you do have a hard
time dealing with other people, M4.

00:07:41.040 --> 00:07:45.750
But I think that's part of what makes
you unique. Wouldn't you agree?"

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:48.500
Sounds like a mom, all right...

00:08:14.910 --> 00:08:16.700
That's definitely it.

00:08:16.700 --> 00:08:19.120
The IBN 5100...

00:08:19.120 --> 00:08:23.160
Then is he FB?

00:08:23.160 --> 00:08:24.500
No.

00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:28.200
FB is a woman.

00:08:43.660 --> 00:08:45.540
He's...!

00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:12.250
Damn!

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:18.370
What's wrong?

00:09:18.370 --> 00:09:20.870
I'll explain later.

00:09:53.830 --> 00:09:57.160
Mr. Braun...

00:10:06.790 --> 00:10:10.580
-Say, how long since you last drove?
-Since I got my license.

00:10:10.580 --> 00:10:13.120
Let's take it nice and easy, then.

00:10:15.120 --> 00:10:18.450
Do you recognize that man?

00:10:18.450 --> 00:10:20.160
I've never seen him before.

00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:23.580
What does this mean?

00:10:32.950 --> 00:10:36.160
In four days, on August 15!

00:10:36.160 --> 00:10:39.080
The world has set your death in stone!

00:10:39.080 --> 00:10:41.160
There's no escaping it!

00:11:20.250 --> 00:11:22.370
A plane headed to France...

00:11:22.370 --> 00:11:24.580
That's where SERN is.

00:11:24.580 --> 00:11:27.790
We didn't see any women
who could've been FB.

00:11:30.830 --> 00:11:32.580
You can at least call!

00:11:32.580 --> 00:11:35.160
I've had my hands full.

00:11:35.160 --> 00:11:37.200
I personally don't care.

00:11:37.200 --> 00:11:39.160
It's just...

00:11:40.410 --> 00:11:43.200
It's Mayuri who's...

00:11:43.200 --> 00:11:47.870
Now that you mention it, I feel like
I haven't talked to her in a long time.

00:11:47.870 --> 00:11:50.910
She said the same thing.

00:11:50.910 --> 00:11:52.750
I'm sorry.

00:11:55.700 --> 00:11:58.000
-Let's go.
-Huh?

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:59.620
Our only option is to confront him directly.

00:11:59.620 --> 00:12:02.750
Confront who?

00:12:02.750 --> 00:12:05.830
Someone we know very well.

00:12:19.660 --> 00:12:22.750
Oh! What brings you
here so early in the morning?

00:12:24.040 --> 00:12:25.870
Well, come in.

00:12:26.790 --> 00:12:28.910
So, what do you want?

00:12:28.910 --> 00:12:33.200
Come to pay the extra
6,000 yen on your rent, huh?

00:12:34.250 --> 00:12:37.580
Hey, this is the part where
you're supposed to butt in and say,

00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:40.910
"That's 1,000 yen more than you said!"

00:12:42.830 --> 00:12:44.450
I would like to ask you something.

00:12:44.450 --> 00:12:47.120
Geez, why so formal?

00:12:48.080 --> 00:12:52.500
You know about someone
named "FB," do you not?

00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:54.910
We've seen everything.

00:12:54.910 --> 00:12:58.790
Including the IBN 5100
being hauled away from here.

00:13:00.450 --> 00:13:05.660
We mean you no harm.
We simply wish to meet with FB.

00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:08.870
Please, tell us. Where can we find her?

00:13:14.870 --> 00:13:18.040
Looks like you're a traitor, M4.

00:13:18.950 --> 00:13:22.040
FB gave me that code name...

00:13:22.040 --> 00:13:25.000
It's a secret name only FB and I know...

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:27.790
-Are you saying...?!
-How can that be?!

00:13:27.790 --> 00:13:31.370
Ever heard of Ferdinand Braun?

00:13:31.370 --> 00:13:34.750
The Nobel Prize physicist
who invented the CRT?

00:13:34.750 --> 00:13:36.160
Impressive.

00:13:36.160 --> 00:13:38.450
And what are his initials?

00:13:38.450 --> 00:13:40.750
"F.B."...

00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:43.250
So you're...?!

00:13:44.450 --> 00:13:47.580
No... That's not possible...

00:13:47.580 --> 00:13:51.370
First, overdependence, and now escapism?

00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:54.330
Nae is asleep. Let's go elsewhere.

00:13:59.870 --> 00:14:04.910
This damn city just keeps changin'.

00:14:04.910 --> 00:14:07.330
Are you really FB?

00:14:07.330 --> 00:14:08.870
Yeah.

00:14:08.870 --> 00:14:11.870
But the e-mails...!

00:14:11.870 --> 00:14:14.160
I wrote 'em all.

00:14:15.410 --> 00:14:17.410
Why did I write like a woman?

00:14:17.410 --> 00:14:20.200
To fool you, of course.

00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:22.370
-That can't be--
-It ain't just you.

00:14:22.370 --> 00:14:24.410
I do it with the others, too.

00:14:24.410 --> 00:14:28.910
I send them e-mails pretending
to be whoever they most need.

00:14:28.910 --> 00:14:35.160
It helps that people like
you are also the easiest to trick.

00:14:35.160 --> 00:14:37.910
Why'd you cut off contact with her?

00:14:37.910 --> 00:14:42.410
She outlived her usefulness the
moment she found the IBN 5100.

00:14:42.410 --> 00:14:44.790
So I got rid of her.

00:14:44.790 --> 00:14:47.450
We gather members using text messages.

00:14:47.450 --> 00:14:49.910
People like that are easiest to deal with...

00:14:49.910 --> 00:14:52.500
...and easiest to get rid of
once they're no longer useful.

00:14:52.500 --> 00:14:55.580
They have nowhere they belong, after all.

00:14:55.580 --> 00:14:58.080
I can't believe you're a SERN lapdog...

00:14:58.080 --> 00:14:59.580
A dog?

00:14:59.580 --> 00:15:01.370
Suzuha didn't...

00:15:01.370 --> 00:15:04.410
Hashida Suzu-san didn't take care of you

00:15:04.410 --> 00:15:06.580
so you could go and do this!

00:15:07.910 --> 00:15:11.750
How do you know Suzu-san?

00:15:13.540 --> 00:15:16.330
This has nothing to do with her.

00:15:16.330 --> 00:15:18.330
This has nothing to do with Suzu-san!

00:15:18.330 --> 00:15:21.200
-But...!
-What would you know?!

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:34.080
You ever slept in a manhole
in the middle of winter?

00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:36.000
I was still just a kid...

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:40.290
The concrete was freezing.
Bone-chillingly cold.

00:15:40.290 --> 00:15:43.080
I wouldn't eat for
three or four days at a time.

00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:47.830
And whenever I'd lie down, they would come...

00:15:47.830 --> 00:15:49.370
Huh?

00:15:49.370 --> 00:15:50.370
The rats.

00:15:50.370 --> 00:15:53.660
They'd gnaw at me,
mistaking me for a corpse.

00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:59.910
That's when I saw a thread dangling down.

00:15:59.910 --> 00:16:01.580
A spider's thread...

00:16:01.580 --> 00:16:04.500
I had to climb up it, y'know?

00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:10.120
Even if following it meant
getting my hands dirty.

00:16:15.160 --> 00:16:19.120
So I climbed the thread...

00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:22.580
And before I knew it,
I was a puppet on strings.

00:16:24.700 --> 00:16:27.910
There's no escape.

00:16:27.910 --> 00:16:31.250
Once a puppet breaks loose from its strings...

00:17:15.830 --> 00:17:18.910
"Traitors get death," as they say.

00:17:18.910 --> 00:17:23.660
Well, they off you after you've
served your purpose, anyway.

00:17:23.660 --> 00:17:26.250
You called me a dog earlier.

00:17:26.250 --> 00:17:28.040
We ain't dogs.

00:17:28.040 --> 00:17:30.250
We're livestock.

00:17:31.330 --> 00:17:35.200
I thought about escaping before.

00:17:35.200 --> 00:17:40.250
But now I have something precious to me.

00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:43.700
I didn't wanna drag her into this.

00:17:43.700 --> 00:17:47.750
But... failure isn't allowed.

00:17:47.750 --> 00:17:51.410
Try to run, and they'll
go after your family too.

00:17:53.790 --> 00:17:56.410
I've failed, too.

00:17:56.410 --> 00:17:59.660
But Nae doesn't know a thing.

00:18:02.700 --> 00:18:04.950
If I just die...

00:18:05.700 --> 00:18:07.080
Wait--!

00:18:30.830 --> 00:18:34.870
O-Okabe... kun...

00:18:35.870 --> 00:18:39.040
Okabe-kun...

00:18:42.660 --> 00:18:45.120
S-Sorry...

00:18:47.450 --> 00:18:51.290
I'm... sorry...

00:18:59.290 --> 00:19:02.330
O-Okabe! His phone!

00:19:02.330 --> 00:19:03.910
The D-mail!

00:19:03.910 --> 00:19:05.580
Okabe!

00:19:12.540 --> 00:19:14.500
"To: M4"
"IBN5100 search off. Stand by, do nothing."

00:19:27.160 --> 00:19:30.000
Moeka...?

00:19:32.200 --> 00:19:33.830
"From: S.F." "Subject: (No subject)"
"I won't need the IBN 5100 for a while after all. Moeka"

00:19:33.830 --> 00:19:37.540
You don't need it...?

00:19:40.500 --> 00:19:42.250
"From: S.F." "Subject: (No subject)"
"My boss put a hold on things. Moeka"

00:19:44.410 --> 00:19:46.450
Hello, this is Urushibara!

00:19:46.450 --> 00:19:48.660
Oh, Kyouma-s-

00:19:49.120 --> 00:19:52.160
Huh? An IBN 5100?

00:19:52.160 --> 00:19:54.040
Actually, we do!

00:19:56.410 --> 00:19:58.580
This is it...!

00:20:01.290 --> 00:20:02.250
Daru!

00:20:02.250 --> 00:20:03.830
Hashida's not here.

00:20:03.830 --> 00:20:06.290
He said he's going to Comima, remember?

00:20:08.910 --> 00:20:10.330
I beg you!

00:20:10.330 --> 00:20:12.830
Hear my request!

00:20:15.830 --> 00:20:17.660
I see.

00:20:17.660 --> 00:20:21.660
The only way to prevent Mayuri's
death is to leave this alpha world line

00:20:21.660 --> 00:20:27.290
and return to the world line that
exists before you send your first D-mail...

00:20:27.290 --> 00:20:29.580
The beta world line, in other words.

00:20:29.580 --> 00:20:31.620
And the only way to do that

00:20:31.620 --> 00:20:34.700
is to delete that data
from SERN's database.

00:20:34.700 --> 00:20:36.540
All this stuff about Mayushii dying

00:20:36.540 --> 00:20:39.410
and Miss Amane being my future daughter...

00:20:39.410 --> 00:20:43.700
If this is all just in your head, you
could totally be a light novel author!

00:20:43.700 --> 00:20:45.830
Nothing would make me happier.

00:20:45.830 --> 00:20:47.620
Do you believe it, Miss Makise?

00:20:47.620 --> 00:20:49.200
As a hypothesis, at least.

00:20:49.200 --> 00:20:54.950
I'd love some actual, objective data,
but that's obviously impossible.

00:20:54.950 --> 00:20:58.580
The time leap machine
you built worked perfectly.

00:20:58.580 --> 00:21:01.580
Huh? R-Really?

00:21:01.580 --> 00:21:04.250
I mean, o-of course it did!

00:21:04.250 --> 00:21:06.120
Not to mention...

00:21:08.540 --> 00:21:10.330
What?

00:21:10.330 --> 00:21:13.040
-Never mind.
-Wh-What?!

00:21:13.040 --> 00:21:14.080
I said never mind.

00:21:14.080 --> 00:21:16.080
All hooked up!

00:21:16.080 --> 00:21:20.290
I gotta config some stuff, but
we'll be good to go in 10 minutes.

00:21:20.290 --> 00:21:22.120
We're counting on you, Super hax0r!

00:21:22.120 --> 00:21:24.200
"Super hacker"!

00:21:25.040 --> 00:21:26.950
The first D-mail, huh?

00:21:26.950 --> 00:21:31.910
That's the one where you said
I got stabbed or whatever, wasn't it?

00:21:34.080 --> 00:21:38.200
I bet you tried to feel me up, huh?

00:21:42.330 --> 00:21:47.580
Undoing all our D-mails will
return us to the original world line.

00:21:47.580 --> 00:21:53.500
A world line where SERN's
dystopia never occurs...

00:21:53.500 --> 00:21:56.540
A world line where Mayuri lives...

00:21:56.540 --> 00:22:00.250
And a world line where...

00:22:02.830 --> 00:22:04.540
...Makise Kurisu...

00:22:08.330 --> 00:22:09.330
...dies.

00:22:20.830 --> 00:22:23.830
kisei sareta

00:22:23.830 --> 00:22:29.580
shikai mujihi naru

00:22:29.580 --> 00:22:32.660
juuni no

00:22:32.660 --> 00:22:37.330
shihai nogarerarenai

00:22:37.330 --> 00:22:41.410
ansoku no

00:22:41.410 --> 00:22:46.200
asu o negatta

00:22:46.200 --> 00:22:50.450
te no naka no

00:22:50.450 --> 00:22:54.910
toutoi jishou no chihei e

00:22:54.910 --> 00:22:59.120
torawareshi meiyaku

00:22:59.120 --> 00:23:03.540
arawareta gishou no rinkaku

00:23:03.540 --> 00:23:07.790
seimei no tenchi wa

00:23:07.790 --> 00:23:12.660
moumoku na jikan o kizanda

00:23:12.660 --> 00:23:18.080
habatake batafurai kiseki no batafurai

00:23:18.080 --> 00:23:21.540
anata e sasagu

00:23:21.540 --> 00:23:26.000
namida no batafurai mabushii batafurai

00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:28.700
subete ga

00:23:28.700 --> 00:23:33.700
ima kakikaerareru

